# CodeKeep Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Game logic in `packages/server` — pure functions, no UI, no network
- Types and constants in `packages/shared` — zero deps
- TUI rendering in `packages/cli` — thin layer over server functions

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any`
- ESM only (`"type": "module"` everywhere)
- Prefer `const` and pure functions over classes
- No hardcoded game numbers — use constants from `@codekeep/shared`

## ASCII Rendering
- Grid: 16 lines of monospace string, not nested Ink Box components
- Characters: `· # % $ @ ^` for game elements
- Colors: 16-color ANSI baseline. Use chalk named colors only (red, green, yellow, cyan, white, gray)
- Always handle terminal resize gracefully (show "too small" if < 80x24)

## Testing
- Vitest for all packages
- Game engine tests: pure input → output, no mocks needed
- TUI tests: ink-testing-library, assert on lastFrame() content
- Raid tests: always verify determinism with seeded RNG

## Keybindings
- hjkl / WASD / arrows for movement
- Enter/e to place, u to upgrade, x to demolish
- [/] to cycle structures, ? for help, q to quit
- Never use Ctrl+key for common actions (terminal conflicts)
